@startuml
' --- whole-map provenance: cycle that introduced each @id ---
' @cycle(USE-VALIDATE-CLI, 0015)
' @id(USE-VALIDATE-CLI)
' @desc(USE-VALIDATE-CLI, "`mdd validate` runs the deterministic structural gate from the CLI. The Commands::Validate arm in mdd-cli discovers the project and calls Project::validate() (the existing engine over both current/ and objective/: id presence/uniqueness, per-side @ref resolution, trace-link + use-case->sequence integrity, source_link existence, the @sec contract). Text mode prints error/warning lines and a VALIDATION: PASSED/FAILED summary; `--json` prints a slim {ok, errors, warnings} object. Exit is non-zero only when report.ok is false; readiness warnings (approvals, tests, SVGs) never block. It does not invoke review. Realized by SEQ-VALIDATE-CLI; owned by CMP-VALIDATE-CLI.")
' Current use case (cycle 0015): the structural gate now has a real
' CLI entry point; the /mdd-validate skill calls it instead of
' re-deriving the checklist by inspection.
title MDD validate CLI — deterministic structural gate (current)

left to right direction

actor "Developer / Agent" as Dev

rectangle "mdd toolchain" {
  usecase "Run the structural gate\nfrom the CLI\n(mdd validate)" as ValidateCli
  usecase "Emit a machine-readable\nverdict (--json)" as ValidateJson
}

Dev --> ValidateCli
Dev --> ValidateJson

ValidateCli ..> ValidateJson : <<extend>>

note bottom of ValidateCli
  Current (USE-VALIDATE-CLI): Commands::Validate ->
  Project::validate(). Exit 0 when report.ok, non-zero
  on a blocking structural error. Independent of review.
end note

note bottom of ValidateJson
  --json emits {ok, errors, warnings} via serde_json,
  excluding the ModelRegistry, so the skill parses a
  stable contract.
end note
@enduml
